(9. Consumer withdrawal rights) Tj
T* (For consumer distance service contracts, the statutory withdrawal framework may apply.) Tj
T* (The consumer normally has 14 days to withdraw from the contract, starting from the day) Tj
T* (the contract is concluded, unless a statutory exception applies.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The consumer must receive withdrawal information and the model withdrawal form before) Tj
T* (being bound. If legally required information is omitted, the withdrawal period may be) Tj
T* (extended under applicable law.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Not every service always carries a withdrawal right, and not every service automatically) Tj
T* (loses it. Any exception must be assessed for the specific service and the statutory) Tj
T* (conditions that apply to that service.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (10. Early commencement) Tj
T* (Beginning during the withdrawal period requires a separate express consumer request. The) Tj
T* (early-start request must not be bundled into general Terms acceptance.) Tj
T* () Tj
